<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>VA Claims Flowchart</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .option {
      margin: 10px 0;
      padding: 12px;
      border: 2px solid #1e3a8a;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #f9fafb;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 0.3s;
    }
    .option:hover {
      background: #e0e7ff;
    }
    .content {
      display: none;
      margin-top: 10px;
      padding: 10px;
      border-left: 4px solid #1e3a8a;
      background: #f3f4f6;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Choose Your Claim Path</h1>
  
  <div class="option" onclick="toggleContent('newClaim')">
    ➤ New Claim
    <div id="newClaim" class="content">
      <p>If you’ve never filed before or are filing for a new condition, start here.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="option" onclick="toggleContent('supplementalClaim')">
    ➤ Supplemental Claim
    <div id="supplementalClaim" class="content">
      <p>If your claim was denied but you have new evidence, this is the right option.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="option" onclick="toggleContent('higherReview')">
    ➤ Higher-Level Review
    <div id="higherReview" class="content">
      <p>If you disagree with a decision and want a senior reviewer to look at it, choose this.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <script>
    function toggleContent(id) {
      // hide all sections first
      document.querySelectorAll('.content').forEach(c => c.style.display = 'none');
      // show only the clicked one
      document.getElementById(id).style.display = 'block';
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
